âš™ï¸ 3. Features of Java

Java is famous for its powerful features that make it robust, secure, and platform-independent.

Feature	Description
Simple	Easy to learn, especially for C/C++ programmers. No pointers, header files, or multiple inheritance confusion.
Object-Oriented	Everything in Java is an object â€” supports encapsulation, inheritance, and polymorphism.
Platform-Independent	Write Once, Run Anywhere â€” code runs on any OS with JVM.
Secure	No explicit pointers, built-in security features, bytecode verification, and sandboxing.
Robust	Strong memory management, exception handling, and type checking at compile and runtime.
Multithreaded	Supports concurrent execution of multiple threads.
Portable	Java code behaves consistently across all platforms.
High Performance	Bytecode is optimized by Just-In-Time (JIT) compiler.
Dynamic	Supports runtime linking and dynamic class loading.
Distributed	Enables communication through APIs like RMI and networking libraries.
